    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                <head>No. 150.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Williams</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-08-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 29,
                            1874</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 180.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I transmit herewith, for your information and
                        that of Mr. Avery, a copy of an instruction of the 26th instant, No. 65,
                        which has been addressed to John A. Bingham, esq., the minister of the
                        United States in Japan,<note n="*" xml:id="d152fn1">See correspondence with
                            the minister to Japan.</note> with an inclosure, both relating to the
                        subject of co-operative action between the United States and other western
                        powers in that country.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
